# Documentation First (DoctorProCare Backend)

Before modifying code under `Hospital-Management-API/`:

1. Read the target app's `AI_CONTEXT.md`
2. Read `docs/BUSINESS_FLOW.md` and the relevant layer file (MODELS, API, WORKFLOWS)
3. Check `shared_docs/status_registry.md` and `shared_docs/INVARIANTS.md`

When changing code:

- Update `{app}/docs/` in the same PR (see `docs/CONTRIBUTING.md`)
- New status enums → `shared_docs/status_registry.md`
- New feature flags → `shared_docs/CONFIGURATION.md`
- Architectural decisions → `{app}/docs/DECISIONS.md` as ADR-NNN

Do not duplicate glossary or status definitions in app docs — link to `shared_docs/`.

Planning documents still go to `HOS_API/docs/`; distill outcomes into app docs when implemented.

Read order: `AGENTS.md` → `shared_docs/glossary/` → `{app}/AI_CONTEXT.md` → `{app}/docs/`.
